{"type": "root", "attrs": {"tags": "cloudfx", "icon": "SHELF/cloudrig"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cloud Rig"], "extent": [0, 14]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Converts geometry into a cloud, complete with lighting."], "extent": [53, 116]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [116, 131], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool converts the selected geometry into a cloud-like ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/model/volumes", "type": "link", "text": ["VDB volume"], "fullpath": "/model/volumes"}, " \ncomplete with lighting. This tool can be useful for creating an individual \ncloud, or simply as a demo for the lower-level tools ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/cloud", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/cloud"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloud", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloud"}, ", ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/cloudnoise", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/cloudnoise"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise"}, ", and ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/cloudlight", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/cloudlight"}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight"}, "."], "extent": [131, 509]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["How to"], "extent": [509, 522], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create a cloud-like volume"], "role": "item", "extent": [522, 557], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object you want to convert to a cloud volume."], "extent": [557, 630]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["On the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cloud FX"]}, " shelf tab, click ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/cloudrig", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/cloudrig"}, " Cloud Rig."], "extent": [630, 711]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The rig tool sets up several nodes in the scene."], "extent": [711, 769]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["The Cloud Rig tool hides the original geometry object and creates a new object (", {"type": "code", "text": ["cloud_from_", {"type": "var", "text": ["name"]}]}, ") that references the geometry from the object you selected."], "extent": [769, 942]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["It adds a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloud", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloud"}, ", ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise"}, ", and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight"}, " inside the new geometry object. See the help pages for those nodes for how to use their parameters."], "extent": [942, 1160]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["It adds a key ", {"type": "q", "text": ["sun"]}, " light (", {"type": "code", "text": ["sunlight"]}, ") and environment light with a sky texture (", {"type": "code", "text": ["skylight"]}, ") to light the cloud."], "extent": [1160, 1284]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["It assigns the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/cloud", "type": "link", "text": ["cloud material"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/cloud"}, " to the new object."], "extent": [1284, 1378]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["It wires a reference to the sun light\u2019s position into the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight"}, " node. The cloud light node uses the light position to add attributes to the cloud that are then used by the shader to simulate light scattering through the cloud."], "extent": [1378, 1640]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1640, 1649], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloud", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloud"}], "extent": [1649, 1675]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudnoise"}], "extent": [1675, 1711]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight", "type": "link", "text": ["Cloud Light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cloudlight"}], "extent": [1711, 1749]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Cloud Rig"], "summary": ["Converts geometry into a cloud, complete with lighting."]}